Magic Strings (Programming)

We have an integer M and an array of size K with strings (all lowercase a-z). Each string will have more than 1 character and less than 105 characters. We perform this operation on each string:

(ASCII value of character at position 0)M * (ASCII value of char. at 1)M  *... * (ASCII value of char. at string.length-1)M

For example, if the string is "ab" we would follow the equation: Given M = 2

(a = 97)M * (b = 98)M = (97)2 * (98)2 = 90364036, EVEN

Once we have the number for each string, we sum all numbers together. Can you figure out whether the sum is EVEN or ODD?

Constraints:

1 <= T <= 50, T = Number of test cases
2 <= K <= 20, K = Number of strings in one test case
2 <= M <= 109, M = Given integer

Input:

The first line contains the number of test cases T. Each testcase contains on the first line the numbers M and K. On the second line are K space separated strings.

Sample Input:

2
50 3
aceace ceceaa abdbdbdbakjkljhkjh
47 3
azbde abcher acegk

Sample Output:

EVEN
ODD

YOUR ANSWER
